{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a3edd5ad",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# NESCAC Ice Hockey (M) Principal Component Analysis\n",
    "## 2022-23 through 2025-26 standings and team stats"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b22ffbf1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "from sklearn.manifold import TSNE\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import glob"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Find all CSV files in the current folder\n",
    "csv_files = glob.glob('*.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "df1 = pd.read_csv(csv_files[0]).drop(columns=['Team','Neutral','Neutral Att','Neutral Att Avg','All Att','All Att Avg','All'])\n",
    "df2 = pd.read_csv(csv_files[1]).drop(columns=['Team','Neutral','Neutral Att','Neutral Att Avg','All Att','All Att Avg','All'])\n",
    "df3 = pd.read_csv(csv_files[2]).drop(columns=['Team','Neutral','Neutral Att','Neutral Att Avg','All Att','All Att Avg','All'])\n",
    "df4 = pd.read_csv(csv_files[3]).drop(columns=['Team','Neutral','Neutral Att','Neutral Att Avg','All Att','All Att Avg','All'])"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Clean the data"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "for df in [df1, df2, df3, df4]:\n",
    "    df[['GF','GA']] = df['GF-GA'].str.split(' - ', expand=True).astype(int)\n",
    "    df.drop(columns=['GF-GA'], inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "for df in [df1, df2, df3, df4]:\n",
    "    df[['AVGH','AVGV']] = df['AVG Score'].str.split(' - ', expand=True).astype(float)\n",
    "    df.drop(columns=['AVG Score'], inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "for df in [df1, df2, df3, df4]:\n",
    "    df[['Pen Num','Pen Min']] = df['Pen'].str.split(' - ', expand=True).astype(str)\n",
    "    df.drop(columns=['Pen'], inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "for df in [df1, df2, df3, df4]:\n",
    "    df['Pen Num'] = df['Pen Num'].str.replace('None','0').astype(int)\n",
    "    df['Pen Min'] = df['Pen Min'].str.replace(':00','').astype(int)"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Standardize features before PCA\n",
    "\n",
    "PCA depends on scale. Attendance variables are thousands while percentages are decimals.\n",
    "So we convert each feature to a z-score before running PCA."
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df1['champion'] = (df1['Standing'] == 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "features = [\n",
    "    col for col in df1.select_dtypes(include='number').columns\n",
    "    if col not in ['Standing','champion']\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(df1[features])\n",
    "\n",
    "features"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## PCA computation"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pca = PCA(n_components=3)\n",
    "scores = pca.fit_transform(X_scaled)\n",
    "\n",
    "pca.explained_variance_ratio_"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "loadings = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "    pca.components_.T,\n",
    "    index=features,\n",
    "    columns=[\"PC1\",\"PC2\",\"PC3\"]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "loadings"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.scatter(scores[:,0], scores[:,1], c=df1['Standing'], cmap='viridis')\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"PC1\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"PC2\")\n",
    "plt.colorbar(label='Standing')\n",
    "plt.title(\"PCA projection\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Side Quest: t-SNE Projection\n",
    "\n",
    "PCA preserves variance.\n",
    "\n",
    "t-SNE preserves neighborhood structure.\n",
    "\n",
    "So instead of asking:\n",
    "\n",
    "> Which directions explain the most variation?\n",
    "\n",
    "it asks:\n",
    "\n",
    "> Which teams are most similar to each other?"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Important interpretation rule\n",
    "\n",
    "In a t-SNE plot:\n",
    "\n",
    "- nearby points are meaningful\n",
    "- clusters may be meaningful\n",
    "- axes are not meaningful\n",
    "- distances between clusters should be interpreted cautiously"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "tsne = TSNE(\n",
    "    n_components=2,\n",
    "    perplexity=3,\n",
    "    learning_rate='auto',\n",
    "    init='pca',\n",
    "    random_state=42\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "tsne_scores = tsne.fit_transform(X_scaled)"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.scatter(tsne_scores[:,0], tsne_scores[:,1], c=df1['Standing'], cmap='viridis')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('t-SNE 1')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('t-SNE 2')\n",
    "plt.colorbar(label='Standing')\n",
    "plt.title('t-SNE projection of NESCAC hockey teams')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Reflection questions\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Which teams are close together in PCA space?\n",
    "2. Which teams are close together in t-SNE space?\n",
    "3. Are the same teams grouped together?\n",
    "4. Which visualization better reveals clusters?\n",
    "5. Which visualization better explains which variables matter?"
   ]
  }

 ],
